---
type Props = {
  totalFinishedBooks: number
  totalYears: number
}

const { totalFinishedBooks, totalYears } = Astro.props
---

<section class="library-intro" aria-labelledby="library-title">
  <h1 id="library-title">Too many books, too little time...</h1>
  <prose-content>
    <p>I enjoy reading—though that may be an understatement.</p>
    <p>
      I read almost everywhere: at home, in the office, in the car, on trains or
      planes—as long as I could stay awake. My favorite place to read is coffee
      shops: good coffee, good book, no agenda. Before traveling somewhere, I
      would pick up a book about the place—its history, culture, people, and
      landscape.
    </p>
    <p>
      I don’t confine myself to any particular genre. I’ve found great reads in
      fiction, children’s literature, biography, memoir, history, politics,
      religion, geography, business, economics, and plenty more.
    </p>
    <p>
      For me, reading is leisure: it keeps my mind active, satisfies my
      curiosity, and offers the best way to relieve stress.
    </p>
    <p>
      This page is where I keep track of that journey:
      {totalFinishedBooks}
      books over the last {totalYears} years.
    </p>
    <blockquote>
      <p>
        I bought a copy of Faulkner’s Light In August and went to the noisiest
        jazz café I could think of, reading my new book while listening to
        Ornette Coleman and Bud Powell and drinking my hot, thick, foul-tasting
        coffee. At five-thirty I closed my book, went outside, and ate a light
        supper. How many Sundays-how many hundreds of Sundays like this-lay
        ahead of me? “Quiet, peaceful, and lonely,” I said aloud to myself. On
        Sundays, I didn’t wind my spring.
      </p>
      <p>— Norwegian Wood, by Haruki Murakami</p>
    </blockquote>
  </prose-content>
</section>

